Deleted paragraph is off topic, speculative, and not appropriate for a biography page. It also appears to be in violation of Wikipedia policies and guidelines. As a previous user noted, the insinuation is based on illegally attained emails protected by FERPA, and the publication of student correspondence is a violation of federal law. User Yspg's claim that "Mahmood never publicly denied the correspondence" is not an acceptable form of evidence, nor grounds to publish material maligning someone's person or politics. Finally, the source appears biased. It should be noted that Yspg has gone to many other pages and insinuated that persons have connections to Turkish President Erdogen. If this user continues too re-publish this paragraph, there seems good reason for editors to address this matter on the talk page.
